REPLACE-ME-WITH-YOUR-AISTUDIO-KEY
# ── Brain backend key for the Talk-to-Alice "gemini:*" models ──────────
#
# 1. Get a key from https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey (free tier
#    available; pick the project you want billed in Google Cloud Console).
# 2. Save your key as the FIRST line of either of:
#       Documents/google_gemini_api.key            (this file, .gitignored)
#       ~/.config/sifta/gemini.key                  (user-config home)
#    or export it to the environment:
#       export GEMINI_API_KEY=sk-...
# 3. Restart `Applications/sifta_talk_to_alice_widget.py`. The brain
#    dropdown will now show `gemini:gemini-2.5-flash` (and friends) at
#    the top. Picking one routes Alice through Google's API for that
#    turn; picking a `*:latest` Ollama model goes back to local Gemma.
# 4. Open `Applications/sifta_gasstation_meter.py` to watch tokens and
#    USD tick in real time. The same `request_tag` appears in
#    Google Cloud Console → "API & Services" → request logs (filter on
#    user-agent prefix `sifta-swarm/`).
#
# Comments below the first non-comment line are ignored by the resolver.
